Police in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) have arrested four suspects at Nyanya for alleged armed robbery and impersonation. A statement issued on Wednesday spokesman Mariam Yusuf said, “Amongst the suspects are one James Salifu and Umar Hamza arrested by detectives from Nyanya during a routine stop and search operation on Sunday. “The suspects who intended to dispossess their unsuspecting victim of his vehicle confessed to being members of an armed robbery syndicate terrorising Nyanya axis. Exhibits recovered from them are two locally-made pistols, four rounds of live ammunition and charms. Police also said two persons were arrested for impersonating military personnel and defrauding members of the public. The two suspects were reportedly caught while attempting rob their victim of his motorcycle along Nyanya bridge. A motorcycle and military camoflague were recorded as exhibits, the police said.